    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-09-22T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-09-22T05:00:00-05:00" n="250"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d250">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/10140: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hayes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-09-22T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 22, 1942—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 22—9:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1407. My 1406, September 22.<note n="56" xml:id="d250fn56">Not printed.</note>
                    Government’s statement of foreign policy is nearly identical with previous
                    similar statements except that the reference to historical solidarity with
                    Hispanic-American countries is new. In view of the fact that all but two of the
                    Hispanic-American countries are either at war or have broken relations with the
                    Axis, this addition to the statement of Spanish foreign policy is very
                    encouraging to our side. Likewise very significant and favorable to us is the
                    emphasis on solidarity with Portugal coming so closely after the Portuguese
                    Government’s statement of moral solidarity with Brazil upon the latter’s entry
                    into the war.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hayes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
